<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-537-419  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 537 419.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 2 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hughes to pursue Korean market with Samsung. (Hughes Aircraft Co.,andO;Samsung Group, satellite system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hughes Aircraft Co. (product development)Samsung Group (product development).andO;Topic:     KoreaSatellite Communications.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HUGHES TO PURSUE KOREAN MARKET WITH SAMSUNG LOS ANGELES, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A.,andO;1990 OCT 2 (NB) -- Hughes Aircraft, the satellite-building unit of GM, willteam up with the Samsung chaebol, or conglomerate, of Korea in a bid toestablish a domestic satellite system for the Korean government.andM;The South Korean government wants to establish a domestic satellite systemwith data, voice and video communications and direct-broadcast televisioncapabilities.andP;  A request for proposals is expected in spring of 1991, with acontract due for award in early 1992 and a satellite launch scheduled for1995.andP;  Samsung will represent Hughes in Korea for sales of satellite earthstation equipment.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900928/Press Contact: Hughes Aircraft, Fran Slimmer,213/414-6363)</TEXT></DOC>